        <mxCell id="OUR46gFcDWLiVBZJXO1W-32" value="Note that the post processor only gets executed if there was no internal error. As the output_generator knows no real errors (except the given internal one), it is up to the developer to control whether the post processor is supposed to get triggered or not. For the large majority of use cases, you do NOT need post processing - therefore, don&#39;t pass along a post processing function to your class&#39; instance unless you really need that functionality" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;" parent="WIyWlLk6GJQsqaUBKTNV-1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="51" y="1004" width="320" height="30" as="geometry" />
